ce:section.ce:para:
As well know, the PBA-involved electrode is easy to dissolve in the alkaline electrolyte, while the neutral electrolyte like Na2SO4 and Li2SO4 can usually provide the PBA electrode excellent cyclic stability but limited specific capacity. Thus, we evaluated the electrochemical properties of the CDs/NiFe PBA NCs-NF electrode in the KOH, Na2SO4 and their mixtures with different ratios. Among all tested electrolytes, the CDs/NiFe PBA NCs-NF electrode shows the best specific capacity in the hybrid electrolyte with 1.3 M Na2SO4 and 0.5 M KOH (in Table S2). A detailed comparison of this hybrid electrolyte with pure 3 M KOH and 1 M Na2SO4 electrolytes was then made to demonstrate its advantages (Fig. 5
                        ). It can be seen from the GCD curves that the discharge time of the electrode in the hybrid electrolyte is longest among the three electrolytes (Fig. 5 a). Not only that, the working voltage of the electrode (0.43 V) in this hybrid electrolyte is also higher than that of pure KOH electrolyte (0.38 V). The calculated Cs
                         for the hybrid electrolyte is superior to that for pure KOH and Na2SO4 electrolyte (Fig. 5 b). In CV curves (Fig. 5 c), the redox potential of the electrode in the hybrid electrolyte is positively shifted by almost ∼100 mV as compared with those of pure KOH electrolyte, which coincides well with the higher discharge platform in GCD curves. Moreover, its polarization current resulted from oxygen evolution is significantly reduced. From the EIS curves (Fig. 5 d) and their corresponding fitting parameters (Table. 1
                        ), the electrode in the hybrid electrolyte has a significantly reduced series resistance (Rs
                        ) than that of pure Na2SO4 electrolyte, meanwhile it displays the smallest charge transfer resistance (Rct
                        ) among all tested electrolytes. In addition, the higher slope at lower frequency for the hybrid electrolyte indicates its better conductivity of the charges within the electroactive materials [44,45]. Based on above results, we thus selected the hybrid electrolyte of 1.3 M Na2SO4 and 0.5 M KOH for the following investigations.
